1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:02,980
[2025 Chungnam location incentive
production support project]

2
00:00:10,990 --> 00:00:13,530
[Woo Jihan]

3
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:18,340
[Shin Jeongyou]

4
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:22,650
[Min Dohee]

5
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,700
[Seo Seunghyeon]

6
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:35,020
[Always Meet Again]

7
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:37,100
Lee Woojin.

8
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:40,620
Did you call me back?

9
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:44,100
Why would I?

10
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:46,950
I was going to go play basketball.

11
00:00:46,950 --> 00:00:47,950
Wanna join?

12
00:00:48,060 --> 00:00:49,320
Come out if you want to.

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:56,480
Why did I come back here

14
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,420
and meet you again?

15
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:06,420
I must

16
00:01:07,610 --> 00:01:08,610
go back.

17
00:01:40,890 --> 00:01:42,620
I barely managed to forget you.

18
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:52,960
Hey, pass!

19
00:01:58,820 --> 00:01:59,880
Transfer student.

20
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:03,630
Are you okay?

21
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:14,130
You don't look well.

22
00:02:17,210 --> 00:02:18,210
I like...

23
00:02:21,490 --> 00:02:25,500
[Episode 2: My Heart beats
for My First Love Again]

24
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:27,490
I like...

25
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:29,680
Suddenly?

26
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,690
Oh.

27
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,900
I mean, like, I'm fine.

28
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,440
So don't worry.

29
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,840
You don't look well though.

30
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:50,780
[Lee Woojin]

31
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:54,340
Did this happen before?

32
00:03:00,670 --> 00:03:02,850
Goodness.

33
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:06,780
I knew something was wrong
when you last came here.

34
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:08,390
Are you sure this is the only wound?

35
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:09,910
Did you hurt your head?

36
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,080
No.

37
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:12,230
I was just confused.

38
00:03:12,970 --> 00:03:13,970
That's not right.

39
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:15,280
You seem crazy.

40
00:03:17,490 --> 00:03:18,400
How much longer will it take?

41
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,400
Almost done.

42
00:03:22,329 --> 00:03:22,960
Oh!

43
00:03:23,350 --> 00:03:24,950
I need to go to the teachers' office.

44
00:03:24,950 --> 00:03:26,280
Here's a Band-Aid. Do it yourself.

45
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,510
Wait for me here.

46
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,910
If anyone comes,
tell them I'll be back soon

47
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:30,120
and just wait. Okay?

48
00:03:30,970 --> 00:03:31,490
Hey!

49
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:33,070
You have to finish what you started.

50
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:34,130
I'll be right back.

51
00:03:35,140 --> 00:03:36,260
So irresponsible.

52
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:40,220
School nurse.

53
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,600
Didn't you say you weren't hurt?

54
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:49,840
Well...

55
00:03:50,490 --> 00:03:51,620
It was fine just now.

56
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:53,040
It just suddenly hurt.

57
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:57,810
One should take care
of their health when they're young

58
00:03:57,810 --> 00:03:59,940
so they won't suffer when they're old.

59
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:01,860
Have you been old before?

60
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:03,370
Of course...

61
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,530
not.

62
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,820
Adults just always say that.

63
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,800
The school nurse
went to the teachers' office.

64
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,210
She said she'll be back soon.

65
00:04:14,210 --> 00:04:14,970
Okay.

66
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:36,110
You need the spray, right?

67
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,190
What?

68
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:41,950
For your wrist, right?

69
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:43,630
How did you know?

70
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,030
It's normal for someone
who plays basketball

71
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,230
to hurt their wrists.

72
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:49,580
You seem to know

73
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,820
I often hurt my wrist.

74
00:04:54,450 --> 00:04:55,450
Do you...

75
00:04:59,010 --> 00:05:00,040
like me?

76
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,180
What are you talking about?

77
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:21,170
Is that not it?

78
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:24,190
Then how do you know me so well?

79
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,490
I don't.

80
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:32,230
You say you don't,

81
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:34,530
but actually you know me well.

82
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,390
Did you put the Band-Aid on?

83
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:51,690
Nurse!

84
00:05:51,690 --> 00:05:53,490
Since you're back, I'm leaving.

85
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,510
Thank you!

86
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:56,760
You should put on the Band-Aid first!

87
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,770
I don't want to get involved with him,

88
00:05:58,770 --> 00:06:00,500
but why does it keep happening?

89
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,090
I'll bring it to him.

90
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,250
We are classmates.

91
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:06,870
Oh.

92
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:07,750
Can you?

93
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:08,270
Yes.

94
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,710
Thank you.

95
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:15,310
I should avoid him from now on.

96
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:35,550
Do I really have to avoid him like this?

97
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,520
I'm so hungry.

98
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:58,580
This place is full of memories.

99
00:07:03,140 --> 00:07:04,140
Hello.

100
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,850
Give me a can of coke.

101
00:07:09,750 --> 00:07:10,750
I'm hungry.

102
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:13,570
2,500 won.

103
00:07:14,790 --> 00:07:16,000
I'll pay with my phone.

104
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,390
What?

105
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:18,080
We only take cash here.

106
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,110
Wait.

107
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,360
Do you...

108
00:07:29,710 --> 00:07:30,710
take this too?

109
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:35,970
You're not an elementary school kid.
How could you bring counterfeit notes?

110
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:47,250
I didn't see you eating during lunch.

111
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:49,820
Well,

112
00:07:50,690 --> 00:07:51,890
I wasn't hungry then.

113
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,460
And you say you're not hungry?

114
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,580
You're full of lies.

115
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:01,750
That's not it.

116
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,770
I'll find out if we meet more often.

117
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:05,900
Meet who?

118
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:09,520
You.

119
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:13,670
Why?

120
00:08:15,470 --> 00:08:17,400
We're classmates. Can we not meet?

121
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,020
You...

122
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,210
don't want to see me?

123
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:36,490
This alley

124
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,030
is still the same.

125
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,270
Oh?

126
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:44,280
Wow, I heard this place
was gone after we graduated.

127
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:45,370
How interesting.

128
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:48,750
Oh!

129
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,120
Wow!

130
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:52,190
Gosh, I used to...

131
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:53,720
I used to come here all the time.

132
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,300
The minced meat sauce here

133
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:56,700
is super good.

134
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,860
Skipping class
on his first day of transfer.

135
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,720
How interesting.

136
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,500
I'm hungry.

137
00:09:20,670 --> 00:09:21,670
Gosh.

138
00:09:25,330 --> 00:09:26,330
Gosh.

139
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:29,200
Why does it have to be a 50,000 note?

140
00:09:30,350 --> 00:09:31,530
I can't even use it.

141
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:35,610
Gosh.

142
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:37,910
But this place is still the same.

143
00:10:03,810 --> 00:10:04,860
Done painting already?

144
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:05,410
Yeah.

145
00:10:06,930 --> 00:10:08,130
This is for me, right?

146
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,740
No.

147
00:10:09,990 --> 00:10:11,120
I'm going to keep it.

148
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:11,950
Why?

149
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:13,910
This is your first time drawing me.

150
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,610
Give it to me.

151
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:16,950
You can just draw again.

152
00:10:17,260 --> 00:10:17,970
No.

153
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,090
This is my first time drawing you.

154
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:20,060
I want to keep it.

155
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:21,200
Huh?

156
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:22,700
What do you mean?

157
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,620
You're over if I catch you.

158
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:03,050
This place is nice.

159
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:05,350
How did you know this place?

160
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,180
Well...

161
00:11:07,420 --> 00:11:08,820
Somehow we ended up here.

162
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:15,030
Have this.

163
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,040
Wow!

164
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,440
Thanks.

165
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,040
Oh.

166
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:34,130
This.

167
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,930
The school nurse asked you to put it on.

168
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,100
Let me see.

169
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,480
Does it hurt?

170
00:11:54,970 --> 00:11:55,970
Is it okay?

171
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:07,880
I...

172
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,240
thought about it.

173
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,320
About what?

174
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,560
I'm sure

175
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:16,080
you like me.

176
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:17,850
You're so suspicious.

177
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:19,380
I don't like you.

178
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,000
You like me.

179
00:12:21,190 --> 00:12:22,190
No.

180
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:23,910
Doesn't seem like you don't like me.

181
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:24,820
I said I don't.

182
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:25,850
So I was right.

183
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,510
Huh?

184
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:30,660
What?

185
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,520
I knew it.

186
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,280
Hey, what are you hiding?

187
00:12:36,820 --> 00:12:37,820
What...

188
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:39,540
can I be hiding?

189
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:42,920
You're really suspicious.

190
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,200
Did you do something wrong to me?

191
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,560
I guess.

192
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,100
How could you do that to someone you like?

193
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:55,420
Anyway,

194
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,230
I'll keep an eye on you.

195
00:12:59,370 --> 00:13:00,400
Don't.

196
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,020
Hey. You liked me on your own accord.

197
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:05,240
I can do things on my own accord too.

198
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:12,900
I'm leaving.

199
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:15,690
See you tomorrow.

200
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:18,950
Oh,

201
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,950
be careful of your wound.

202
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,570
See you at school tomorrow.

203
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,800
Since I'm here,

204
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:41,460
it's okay if I stay a little longer,
right?

205
00:14:17,070 --> 00:14:18,070
Water.

206
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:19,820
Oh?

207
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:33,050
When one's upset, they got to drink beer.

208
00:14:43,810 --> 00:14:44,750
Hey, are you crazy?

209
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:45,600
What are you doing?

210
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,860
What's wrong with you?

211
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:49,210
You little brat.

212
00:14:56,850 --> 00:14:57,850
Right.

213
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,180
Hey.

214
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:03,260
I knew something was wrong with you
at school.

215
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,200
Did you get a heatstroke?

216
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:07,420
Well...

217
00:15:13,220 --> 00:15:14,220
Sister.

218
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:16,210
Well,

219
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,880
do you know when
the art room's renovation will be done?

220
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,410
How did you know about that?

221
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:22,680
Well,

222
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,490
can you ask the art teacher

223
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:27,310
and get me the key to the art room?

224
00:15:27,470 --> 00:15:28,470
What?

225
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:29,510
What for?

226
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,810
I ran an errand for someone today

227
00:15:31,810 --> 00:15:34,560
and left my sketchbook there.

228
00:15:34,990 --> 00:15:35,990
Buy a new one.

229
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:37,850
That sketching book

230
00:15:37,850 --> 00:15:38,920
is quite important.

231
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,920
I need it.

232
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:40,810
Seriously.

233
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,050
I'm always in the infirmary.

234
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,790
I'm not familiar with the art teacher.

235
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:46,600
Hey, just wait
until its renovation is done.

236
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,850
I'll be fine in a few days.

237
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:49,800
I need it quickly!

238
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:50,970
As a school nurse,

239
00:15:50,970 --> 00:15:52,090
you can't even help me with this?

240
00:15:52,090 --> 00:15:52,720
What?

241
00:15:52,770 --> 00:15:53,780
You're so useless.

242
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:54,160
Goodness.

243
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,260
What can you even do at school?

244
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:56,260
How dare you!

245
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:59,310
He's so rude.

246
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:24,060
[Jang Hyeseong]

247
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:35,190
You know the test
is coming up, right?

248
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:38,220
I'll score according to the success rate
of free throws.

249
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:39,410
Try your best, okay?

250
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:41,000
-Okay.
-Okay.

251
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,040
Let's go!

252
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:45,690
I'm depressed.

253
00:16:45,910 --> 00:16:47,310
I can't score any of them.

254
00:16:48,070 --> 00:16:49,870
I can definitely get full marks.

255
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:51,810
You're so annoying.

256
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:56,780
By the way,

257
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,910
is the transfer student
good at basketball?

258
00:17:02,610 --> 00:17:04,810
Taking a basketball test at this age...

259
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:07,369
How speechless.

260
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:13,880
We

261
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,980
won't show mercy

262
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:17,390
to the transfer student.

263
00:17:19,190 --> 00:17:20,190
Go and practice.

264
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:22,250
Okay.

265
00:17:44,870 --> 00:17:45,730
Let me help you.

266
00:17:48,450 --> 00:17:50,210
Relax your wrist.

267
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,340
The angle should be like this.

268
00:18:07,450 --> 00:18:08,230
And...

269
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:11,510
Throw hard.

270
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:15,040
Okay.

271
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:16,110
Try it.

272
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:16,800
Okay.

273
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:23,280
Wow!

274
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,960
Hey, I got it!

275
00:18:24,990 --> 00:18:25,990
Well done.

276
00:18:33,890 --> 00:18:34,890
Gosh.

277
00:18:36,980 --> 00:18:38,340
[Lee Woojin]

278
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:43,600
What?

279
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:47,670
With this ball, it'll definitely go in.

280
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:51,420
[Lee Woojin]

281
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:54,860
What's different about it?

282
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:56,790
Because I always use this to shoot.

283
00:18:57,210 --> 00:18:59,150
That's because you're good at it.

284
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,040
If you don't trust me, try it.

285
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:05,460
Your hand

286
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,600
should be here.

287
00:19:09,310 --> 00:19:10,520
Relax your wrist.

288
00:19:14,470 --> 00:19:15,470
And

289
00:19:15,850 --> 00:19:16,910
as for the angle...

290
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:20,730
It should be like this.

291
00:19:21,730 --> 00:19:22,730
And then

292
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:23,750
toss hard.

293
00:19:25,910 --> 00:19:26,770
Okay.

294
00:19:27,870 --> 00:19:28,870
Try it.

295
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:33,800
Wow!

296
00:19:33,850 --> 00:19:34,540
Hey!

297
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:35,750
It went in!

298
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:37,260
Hey, I told you it'd go in.

299
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:45,190
It's different from before.

300
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,480
Of course.

301
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:47,980
It's all thanks to me.

302
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,650
Is it really because of you?

303
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,510
Of course.

304
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,630
Do you want bigger changes?

305
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:00,900
How?

306
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,540
I'll teach you how to play basketball.

307
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:07,200
I'm sure you'll get everything in
in the future.

308
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:08,970
Hey, I'll go get the ball.

309
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:09,980
Hey—

310
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:30,830
Is this really okay?

311
00:20:32,140 --> 00:20:33,140
Really?

312
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:38,120
But if

313
00:20:40,020 --> 00:20:41,550
it can really be changed...

314
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,130
Are you ready?

315
00:20:52,170 --> 00:20:52,830
Huh?

316
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,170
Yeah.

317
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:57,090
In the next five minutes,

318
00:20:57,220 --> 00:20:58,270
try to get the ball from me.

319
00:20:58,270 --> 00:20:59,400
You can do it, right?

320
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:00,620
Hey!

321
00:21:01,610 --> 00:21:02,670
Are you kidding me?

322
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:03,210
Huh?

323
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:04,850
Of course!

324
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:07,340
I'm afraid it won't be that easy.

325
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:09,890
All right, start!

326
00:21:11,190 --> 00:21:11,980
Darn it.

327
00:21:20,650 --> 00:21:22,180
You're quite interesting.

328
00:21:49,380 --> 00:21:51,040
Hey, wait. Let's take a break.

329
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:52,350
You're already tired?

330
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:53,410
Hey, what "already"?

331
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:54,610
It's been 50 minutes.

332
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:56,790
Didn't you say 5 minutes?

333
00:21:56,980 --> 00:21:59,640
That's 'cause you couldn't
get the ball from me.

334
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:00,970
Whatever.

335
00:22:00,980 --> 00:22:02,080
I can't do it.

336
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:04,130
Hey, are you giving up

337
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:05,220
on the test?

338
00:22:05,230 --> 00:22:06,550
Even if I don't do

339
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:09,150
that test,

340
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:11,800
it won't affect my life in the future.

341
00:22:13,210 --> 00:22:14,740
What are you talking about?

342
00:22:14,790 --> 00:22:16,920
You make it sound like you're an adult.

343
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:22,340
Hey, to be honest,

344
00:22:22,860 --> 00:22:24,590
it's not that I'm like an adult—

345
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:26,180
I'm just old for real.

346
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:29,750
What are you talking about?

347
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,440
What if you really get old in the future?

348
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:37,290
In the future?

349
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:45,480
In the future...

350
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:51,780
what kind of life
do you think you'll live?

351
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,240
Well...

352
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:57,280
There's nothing I really want to do.

353
00:22:58,760 --> 00:22:59,760
I might

354
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,700
just live like this with you.

355
00:23:03,630 --> 00:23:04,630
Why?

356
00:23:05,570 --> 00:23:07,370
I just think hanging out with you

357
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:10,680
is quite fun.

358
00:23:26,660 --> 00:23:27,660
In that case,

359
00:23:30,710 --> 00:23:32,130
shall I just stay here?

360
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,010
Here?

361
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:38,760
Yeah.

362
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:41,680
By your side.

363
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,960
If not, are you running away?

364
00:23:49,570 --> 00:23:51,630
The basketball class isn't over yet.

365
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:16,990
[Lee Woojin: You did well today.
See you at school tomorrow.]

366
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,740
You did well today.

367
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:16,150
See you at school tomorrow.

368
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,160
Tomorrow?

369
00:24:22,820 --> 00:24:24,070
Tomorrow...

370
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:25,870
Tomorrow...

371
00:24:29,770 --> 00:24:31,030
Is this okay?

372
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:32,480
Really?

373
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:58,330
Is he already asleep?

374
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:04,610
You're tired already?

375
00:25:15,330 --> 00:25:17,390
It's understandable he slept early.

376
00:25:17,940 --> 00:25:19,470
Good night, Jang Hyeseong.

377
00:25:28,460 --> 00:25:29,460
Hello.

378
00:26:42,730 --> 00:26:43,790
What are you doing?

379
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:45,140
Did you sleep well?

380
00:26:45,460 --> 00:26:47,060
These songs are pretty good.

381
00:26:49,690 --> 00:26:51,020
What are you doing here?

382
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:53,040
I was going to wait till you woke up.

383
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,530
Why were you waiting for me?

384
00:26:55,930 --> 00:26:58,340
I couldn't wake you up
because you were asleep.

385
00:26:58,340 --> 00:27:00,740
But I couldn't bear
to leave you alone more.

386
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:05,870
Aren't you getting off?

387
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:08,890
We already missed our stop by one stop.

388
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:37,430
Hey, wait!

389
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:41,640
If you're lucky,
you might make it in time.

390
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,330
It's okay to be late once in a while.

391
00:27:44,430 --> 00:27:46,880
Being late once
won't affect your future life.

392
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,380
Hey.

393
00:27:47,450 --> 00:27:48,580
We're almost there.

394
00:27:48,850 --> 00:27:49,390
Let's go!

395
00:27:53,770 --> 00:27:54,770
Hurry!

396
00:27:57,770 --> 00:27:59,740
[Seongjin High School]

397
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,810
Hey!

398
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:02,220
Wait, wait.

399
00:28:02,730 --> 00:28:04,240
I can't do it anymore.

400
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:05,440
No more.

401
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:07,290
Whoever's late pays for snacks.

402
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:10,060
Out of nowhere?

403
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:11,060
That's more fun.

404
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:13,240
Hey!

405
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:14,400
This is cheating!

406
00:28:15,510 --> 00:28:16,510
Come quickly!

407
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:35,910
Okay, 10 seconds left.

408
00:28:41,010 --> 00:28:41,930
Hyeseong.

409
00:28:42,050 --> 00:28:44,020
I'll transfer the opponent's defense
to the left,

410
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,650
and you pass the ball to the right.

411
00:28:45,650 --> 00:28:46,540
Okay?

412
00:29:17,310 --> 00:29:18,070
Hyeseong.

413
00:29:19,210 --> 00:29:19,750
Hey!

414
00:29:19,780 --> 00:29:20,780
Woojin!

415
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:23,470
Hey, Woojin!

416
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:24,430
Hey...

417
00:29:24,490 --> 00:29:25,490
Are you okay?

418
00:29:25,780 --> 00:29:26,780
Hey, I'm sorry.

419
00:29:27,850 --> 00:29:28,850
I'm fine.

420
00:29:28,860 --> 00:29:30,390
You didn't do it on purpose.

421
00:29:32,030 --> 00:29:32,760
Are you okay?

422
00:29:32,850 --> 00:29:34,310
Let's go to the infirmary.

423
00:29:34,350 --> 00:29:35,670
Yes, I'm fine.

424
00:29:36,940 --> 00:29:38,470
Hey, I'm fine. Don't worry.

425
00:29:39,540 --> 00:29:40,610
I'll be back soon.

426
00:29:42,090 --> 00:29:42,880
Sir,

427
00:29:42,900 --> 00:29:44,220
we're going to the infirmary.

428
00:29:44,220 --> 00:29:45,480
Okay, go with him.

429
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:46,490
Yes.

430
00:29:50,050 --> 00:29:51,510
Go back to your positions.

431
00:29:57,620 --> 00:30:00,220
But why would things like this
happen as it did?

432
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:10,150
Let's go.

433
00:30:28,650 --> 00:30:29,650
Hey!

434
00:30:29,810 --> 00:30:30,870
What are you doing?

435
00:30:44,190 --> 00:30:47,120
I thought I was fine being the one
bearing the burden.

436
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:56,600
Are you okay?

437
00:31:34,570 --> 00:31:39,040
[Always Meet Again]

